  "doc_id": "1797",
  "text": "To analyze the circadian expression of a gene that peaks at a different phase than CCR2 , TOC1 RNAi constructs were used to transform Arabidopsis plants expressing the morning-phased clock-controlled reporter CAB2 :: luc [CITATION_1] . Similar to the effect of TOC1 RNAi constructs on CCR2 :: luc expression, the period length of CAB2 :: luc expression was shortened by 3 to 4 h in 95% of the TOC1 RNAi T1 seedlings ( Figure 1D ). The short-period phenotype under constant white light was maintained in T2 (data not shown) and T3 homozygous lines ( Figure 1E , Table 1 ).",
